Description: Fragment of handle of a pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine pink-brown; some mica; probable slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: For parallels see I. Lozanov, PATABS 1 96, pl. 54, 4, illustrating one fron Chirpan, Bulgaria. Others known from the Pnyx, Athens (V. Grace, 'Stamped wne jar fragments', Hesperia, suppl. 10, 1956, 173, no.229).and Samos. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0002)
